INSERT INTO notes VALUES(X'b3948a523d4045938ef38af0e7a531c6','UI update plan',replace('1. See the UI changes.\n2. See the connected endpoint\n3. Find the changes\n4. Find the API\n5. Make the update.\n\nGet the links. \n\n[https://www.figma.com/design/8nUEOV7J33uOG09gRRJLnG/Tranqbay-Web-App-Main?node-id=22816-197559&t=GMrTcYlDj4Yhfyq0-4](https://www.figma.com/design/8nUEOV7J33uOG09gRRJLnG/Tranqbay-Web-App-Main?node-id=22816-197559&t=GMrTcYlDj4Yhfyq0-4) Set Preferences(Post Sign Up)  \n\n**Summary**: No changes needed   \n\n[https://www.figma.com/design/8nUEOV7J33uOG09gRRJLnG/Tranqbay-Web-App-Main?node-id=28908-108510&t=GMrTcYlDj4Yhfyq0-4](https://www.figma.com/design/8nUEOV7J33uOG09gRRJLnG/Tranqbay-Web-App-Main?node-id=28908-108510&t=GMrTcYlDj4Yhfyq0-4) First Time Users\n\n- &nbsp;\n\nhow will I know if the prefernece is set or not \n\n- Most likely use the FE object and since the preference is set will it be for provider account or client or both\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[https://www.figma.com/design/8nUEOV7J33uOG09gRRJLnG/Tranqbay-Web-App-Main?node-id=29151-72470&t=GMrTcYlDj4Yhfyq0-4](https://www.figma.com/design/8nUEOV7J33uOG09gRRJLnG/Tranqbay-Web-App-Main?node-id=29151-72470&t=GMrTcYlDj4Yhfyq0-4) Returning Users','\n',char(10)),'[]','2026-04-08T11:06:13.698454+00:00','2026-04-08T11:39:40.326166+00:00',X'e4a9def41a4247609e8eb54c76d82a3d');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(X'2d84857854d84538b6e30b552e759921','Learning Golang',replace('## Why GO?\n\nIt''s a fast, statically typed, compiled language that feels like a dynamically typed, interpreted language.\n\n  \n\n\n### Hello World. \n\n```\n// go codes are written in packages \n\nimport fmt\n\nfunc main(){\nfmt.Println("Hello, World")\n}\n```\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','\n',char(10)),'["programming","go"]','2026-04-10T21:25:52.225144+00:00','2026-04-10T21:27:46.328101+00:00',X'e4a9def41a4247609e8eb54c76d82a3d');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(X'34f1cffb04314cd09d7cd42f43025fd4','zwhere',replace('- Learn golang \n- Master Rust \n- Master Backend \n- Freelance NodeJs and, Golang and Rust Backend \n- Grow in Systems programming \n- Learn Ocaml\n- &nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n## What your weekly life should look like\n\nSomething like:\n\n- **Daytime (or main focus):** Rust/systems\n- **Evening or blocks:** Freelance work\n- **1 day/week:** Admin + proposals\n\n&nbsp;\n\n### April/May — learning Golang\n\n&nbsp;','\n',char(10)),'["rust","profile"]','2026-04-12T11:25:46.195118+00:00','2026-04-12T11:37:10.813484+00:00',X'ed42af204199419299e0965e2263d49e');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(X'1d844f5ed4ef4f60bc2e9e148d1bfe22','Attack',replace('1. Update content for new private client email\n2. Scope the 2FA to the provider account only\n3. inspect client invitation saying `Failed to load invitation details`\n4. ~~attend to joy~~\n5. Manage page need the base URL and the route for it o be fixed, it is template ID 39\n\n```\n@Emeka Oluwaseun @TOLULOPE ADARAMOTI, Please I need the endpoint  Private client sign-up page is connected to\n\nexample here\nhttps://tolulope-timothy-adaramoti.dev.tranqbay.care/sign-up?redirect=/booking/request/01KNVYEWHB0F87ECH1S5CCQJD1\nEmeka Oluwaseun  [6:06 PM]\nInvitation endpoint \n[6:07 PM]Here /invitations/${invitationCode}/accept\n```\n\n&nbsp;\n\n```html\n            <table role="presentation" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%" style="margin: 32px 0;">\n              <tr>\n                <td align="center">\n                  {{ if eq (lower .Tx.Data.provider.providerType) "private" }}\n                  <a href="{{ .Tx.Data.provider.website_url }}/overview" class="button">Manage Bookings</a>\n                  {{ else }}\n                  <a href="https://tranqbay.health/overview" class="button">Manage Bookings</a>\n                  {{ end }}\n                </td>\n              </tr>\n            </table>\n```\n\nfor provider account, the error says “ failed to verify two-factor status” ?? Where is the error coming from? \n\n&nbsp;\n\n```\nrgwu-OqrW\npcnu-lGFa\nbopc-pDp6\n8pho-cRvb\nf2zz-m5Wp\nvyon-8Bok\nhbta-3kbH\n07ar-rUMD\nuacz-DY8L\nr5vf-niZM\n```\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nNow I have a good picture of the full flow. Here''s my take:\n\n**Currently**, timezone flows like this:\n\n1. `[timezone.rs](http://timezone.rs)` middleware reads `x-timezone` header → defaults to `"UTC"` if absent\n2. Handler calls `set_timezone(timezone)` on the service\n3. Service uses `self.get_timezone()` to set the `unregistered_client` participant''s timezone in the DB\n\n---\n\n**The user''s question: should timezone come from the accessor?**\n\nFor **unregistered clients**, the accessor (`OptionalAuthDto`) has `identifier: None` — there''s no profile to look up a timezone from. The header is the only sensible source for them.\n\nFor **registered clients**, you *could* fetch their stored timezone from the client service, but the current approach (trusting the caller to send `x-timezone`) is typical for API design — the client app knows the user''s local timezone.\n\n---\n\n**What might actually be causing null timezone for unregistered clients:**\n\nLooking at `synchronize_guest_participant` in [booking_repository.rs:5141-5143](vscode-webview://0lqp41ahh3u5m932u0cfi3ll4rqhcqi7if0jbqmu12g9ct5i0e9m/src/repository/booking_repository.rs#L5141-L5143), when it inserts a new participant it omits the `timezone` column entirely:\n\n```sql\nINSERT INTO booking_participant (identifier, booking_identifier, reference, participant_type, is_guest, full_name)\nVALUES (?, ?, ?, ''unregistered_client'', 0, ?)\n\n```\n\nThe `save()` path does pass `timezone` through `CreateParticipantDto`, but `synchronize_guest_participant` doesn''t — that''s a likely source of null timezone.\n\n---\n\nSo to directly answer: no, the timezone for an unregistered client can''t come from the accessor (they have no profile). The fix should be ensuring the `x-timezone` header value flows into `synchronize_guest_participant` as well. Do you want me to implement that?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe plan is to get the timezone saved for an unregistered client, this is done via the booking participant.  \n\nCurrently, we’re getting null mostly because we''re trying to fetch the client timezone from the profile \n\n&nbsp;\n\n### Attack\n\n- Inspect the timezone plugin, see how it is extracting the timezone\n- If it is from a user profile, we need a way to get it from the browser, or equivalent \n- , either reuse the existing timezone or set a x-browser-timezone specifically for the user \n- get this timezone into the system via x-browser timezone self.get_broswer_timezon(), self.set_browser_timezon()\n- pass this request down and ensure it is saved in the participant table \n- &nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n### Timezone\n\n- Try to create a booking as unregistered using Africa/Lagos\n- ensure it is stored in the db \n- ensure it is event , all in the local then check on dev \n- If the issue still happens on dev, then see sendstream.\n- The timezone was only set when `guest_[information.is](http://information.is)_some()`, but when a guest email resolves to an existing registered client (line 1103), `guest_information` becomes `None` even though it was a guest flow — so the timezone was silently dropped before being passed to the repo save.\nFixed in both code paths ([booking_helper_service.rs:1350](vscode-webview://0lqp41ahh3u5m932u0cfi3ll4rqhcqi7if0jbqmu12g9ct5i0e9m/src/service/booking_helper_service.rs#L1350) and [booking_helper_service.rs:1625](vscode-webview://0lqp41ahh3u5m932u0cfi3ll4rqhcqi7if0jbqmu12g9ct5i0e9m/src/service/booking_helper_service.rs#L1625)) to always pass `Some(self.get_timezone())`.  \n\n\n### CLient account \n\n```\n{"message":"received non-success response: 401 - {\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-20T08:03:45.855+00:00\",\"status\":401,\"error\":\"Unauthorized\",\"path\":\"/provider/auth\"}","data":null}\n\n```\n\n&nbsp;','\n',char(10)),'[]','2026-04-13T10:25:37.305854+00:00','2026-04-20T08:08:44.804216+00:00',X'e4a9def41a4247609e8eb54c76d82a3d');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(X'eb83125a55e84308bbe9273dc45c0cd1','Provider client relationship',replace('# the data needed\n\n- We need an endpoint\n- provider name\n- headline - occupation\n\n  \n\n\nWe need a field that returns the last interraction happened, the last time a booking was completed\n\nTo do this, we listened to the booking completed event to update the field \n\n&nbsp;','\n',char(10)),'[]','2026-04-14T11:01:14.735696+00:00','2026-04-14T11:05:08.912389+00:00',X'e4a9def41a4247609e8eb54c76d82a3d');
